or when a bunch of normal folks flood into a previously cozy, boutique online space. When the average person got a high-speed pocket computer that linked them 24/7 to the world of social media, the internet ceased to be the domain of weirdos and hobbyists, and became the town square for our entire society.</p><p> That wasn&#39;t a great change, in my opinion. The human race didn&#39;t evolve to all be in the same room together.早期的互联网是一个非常特殊的时代，当时网络世界主要作为那些不太融入线下世界的人的临时逃避或释放阀；大众社交媒体<a href="https://bfi.uchicago.edu/insight/research-summary/when-product-markets-become-collective-traps-the-case-of-social-media/">将互联网变成了一个集体陷阱</a>，一个你<em>必须</em>去的地方，而不是一个你可以逃走的地方。如果你看一下美国青少年的幸福感图表，你会发现从 90 年代中期到 2000 年代，情况有所好转，然后又急剧恶化： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x