s%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg" width="648" height="431.76444929116684" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:611,&quot;width&quot;:917,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:648,&quot;bytes&quot;:99038,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8549e2ca-f248-4f47-8b5a-f82934e8739f_917x611.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <a href="https://www.axios.com/2024/05/07/poll-students-israel-hamas-protests">Axios</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> Axios has <a href="https://www.axios.com/2024/05/07/poll-students-israel-hamas-protests">some more details</a> from the poll:</p><blockquote><p> Only a small minority (8%) of college students have participated in either side of the protests…</p><p>该调查<strong> </strong>发现<strong> </strong>three times as many college students blame Hamas for the current situation in Gaza than they do President Biden…Some 34% blame Hamas, while 19% blame Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, 12% blame the Israeli people and 12% blame Biden.</p><p> A large majority (81%) of students support holding protesters accountable, agreeing with the notion that those who<strong> </strong>destroyed property or vandalized or illegally occupied buildings should be held responsible by their university, per the survey…A majority also said they oppose the protest tactics: 67% say occupying campus buildings is unacceptable and 58% say it&#39;s not acceptable to refuse a university&#39;s order to disperse…Another 90% said blocking pro-Israel students from parts of campus is unacceptable.</p></blockquote><p> And all this is despite 45% of students saying that they sympathize at least “a little bit” with the protesters&#39; cause.</p><p> Perhaps this isn&#39;t too surprising. Unless we&#39;re in a war, Americans naturally care less about foreign policy than about domestic issues closer to home. But given the results about protest tactics, it seems likely that there&#39;s more at work here. The protesters&#39; general bad behavior and failure to suppress antisemitism, along with the fact that many are <a href="https://twitter.com/thestustustudio/status/1788041873652646213">explicitly pro-war</a> , has probably alienated the silent majority, even among the young generation of Americans. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg" width="630" height="678.266129032258" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:801,&quot;width&quot;:744,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:630,&quot;bytes&quot;:155333,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F64213781-7217-493c-af87-fad7346ab2e5_744x801.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p> No matter what you think of Israel&#39;s war, it should be clear that this kind of thing helps precisely no one. Fortunately, it also means the threat to Biden&#39;s reelection chances in November is probably a lot smaller than the protesters like to claim.</p><p> Meanwhile, the protesters continue to waste any political clout they have. They continue to direct all their hatred at Joe Biden, despite the fact that <a href="https://twitter.com/BarakRavid/status/1788329397520388451">Biden is actively exerting pressure on Israel</a> to restrain itself, even as Trump <a href="https://twitter.com/DrEliDavid/status/1788450575685661089">urges unconditional support</a> for Israel&#39;s war effort.</p><p> In any case, the more data comes in, the more it becomes apparent that the Palestine protests have not set the Zoomer generation on fire with activist passion. Instead, most young people are just quietly waiting for the whole thing to go away.</p><h4> 2. The harms from immigration just keep failing to appear</h4><p> As an immigration supporter, I try to be generous to the skeptics and critics. Any country has a right to let in — or to refuse to let in — whoever it wants. And if people are worried about immigration changing their culture, that&#39;s perfectly legitimate.</p><p> But at the same time, immigration restrictionists also claim lots of <em>economic</em> harms from immigration — lower wages, strains on government finances, etc. And yet these arguments keep getting contradicted by the evidence.</p><p> For example, <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-immigration-doesnt-reduce-wages">plenty of evidence shows</a> that immigration — even low-skilled immigration — doesn&#39;t have a negative effect on the wages or employment prospects of the native-born. <a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w30589">Here&#39;s a recent paper</a> from Michael Clemens and Ethan Lewis with a very “clean” identification method — a randomized visa lottery! — that supports this conclusion:</p><blockquote><p> US firms face a binding quota on visas to employ foreign workers in low-skill occupations outside of agriculture. The government allocates this quota to firms in part through a randomized lottery. We evaluate the marginal impact of the quota on firms entering this lottery in 2021 and 2022, using a novel survey and pre-analysis plan. Firms exogenously authorized to employ more immigrants in low-skill jobs significantly increase production (elasticity 0.20–0.22), investment (1.5–2.1), and the rate of profit (0.15). Because the foreign-native elasticity of substitution in production is very low in the policy-relevant occupations (0.8–2.2), the effect on native employment is zero or positive overall, and positive in rural areas.</p></blockquote><p> The simplest reason for this is that immigration isn&#39;t just a labor supply shock — it&#39;s also a positive labor <em>demand</em> shock, because immigrants buy lots of stuff, which requires labor to produce. But there are probably other reasons, too. <a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w32389">Here&#39;s a new paper</a> from Alessandro Caiumi and Giovanni Peri, which finds that immigration helps native-born Americans to get better jobs:</p><blockquote><p> [W]e calculate that immigration, thanks to native-immigrant complementarity and college skill content of immigrants, had a positive and significant effect between +1.7 to +2.6\% on wages of less educated native workers, over the period 2000-2019 and no significant wage effect on college educated natives. We also calculate a positive employment rate effect for most native workers.</p></blockquote><p> And <a href="https://www.minneapolisfed.org/research/institute-working-papers/the-indirect-fiscal-benefits-of-low-skilled-immigration">a 2020 paper</a> by Mark Colas and Dominik Sachs shows that this upskilling effect could be enough to outweigh the drain on local government resources that low-skilled immigrants are known to cause. Of course, the resource strain happens in the short term, while the indirect and long-term fiscal benefits happen only in the long term. Still, this is one more piece of evidence that immigration is more economically beneficial than the restrictionists claim.</p><p> I&#39;m sure the people who are dead-set against immigration for cultural reasons will still rush to pull out some old study by George Borjas that claims to contradict the growing mound of evidence that immigration is economically beneficial or benign. But with every piece of evidence that accumulates, their protestations are looking more and more forlorn.</p><h4> 3. Battery storage is for real</h4><p> One of the biggest knocks against solar was always the fact that the sun doesn&#39;t shine at night. That is a fair point; in order to have solar power replace natural gas, we&#39;re going to need to figure out a way to store solar energy during the daytime for use at night.</p><p> The most obvious way to store electrical energy is just…a battery. For a long time, solar skeptics have claimed that battery storage is just too expensive to ever be feasible. But batteries, as they so often do, are proving the doubters wrong. California — which has trouble building solar because of NIMBYs, but can build batteries just fine — has been <a href="https://www.energy.ca.gov/news/2023-10/california-sees-unprecedented-growth-energy-storage-key-component-states-clean">building a ton of battery storage</a> for utilities.</p><p> And those batteries are now coming online, and already making a huge difference in how Californians use energy: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg" width="518" height="1024" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/baed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1024,&quot;width&quot;:518,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:74972,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbaed8fa3-1a6c-47d9-aea8-1f2dfa234743_518x1024.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://twitter.com/scolerkolo/status/1787832335485829523">纽约时报</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>Meanwhile, <a href="https://www.canarymedia.com/articles/energy-storage/texas-will-add-more-grid-batteries-than-any-other-state-in-2024">Texas is building even more</a> battery storage than California:</p><blockquote><p> Last year, Texas overtook California in <a href="https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/energy/article/texas-most-utility-scale-solar-power-18447562.php">large-scale solar power capacity</a> . When huge amounts of solar power rush onto the grid, batteries tend to follow. Now, Texas is building more grid batteries than California…Developers are expected to complete 6.4 gigawatts of new grid battery capacity in Texas this year…That&#39;s…as much battery capacity as the entire United States built last year…The projection outpaces the 5.2 gigawatts set to come online in California.</p></blockquote><p> Eventually, batteries will smooth out solar&#39;s daily intermittency curve, allowing solar panels to produce enough energy for both nighttime and cloudy weather.</p><p> Now, <em>seasonal</em> intermittency — the fact that the sun doesn&#39;t shine as much in the winter — is a harder problem to solve, because it will probably never make financial sense to buy giant batteries that only get discharged once a year. The easiest solution here is just to build more solar to compensate for the weaker winter light, but that could run into NIMBY land constraints (especially in California). Or we could go looking for other types of storage.</p><p> And in fact, battery prices are <a href="https://twitter.com/Guay_JG/status/1788553049805373673">still crashing</a> . Part of this is due to Chinese industrial overcapacity, which may not last forever. But thanks to the magic of scaling effects, even if China eventually has to cut back on production, their efforts will have made battery factories permanently better, cheaper, and more efficient.</p><p> In other words, human ingenuity keeps on defeating the techno-pessimists.</p><p> <em>(Financial disclosure: <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/battery-powered-appliances">I am invested</a> in a battery storage company.)</em></p><h4> 4. The US needs to build a bunch of warships in Japan (and Korea)</h4><p> The US has a huge problem building enough ships for its navy. And it doesn&#39;t have much of a commercial shipbuilding industry to speak of. A lot of people are now <a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/national-security/4624326-almost-all-navy-shipbuilding-is-hopelessly-behind-schedule-as-war-looms/">rightfully freaking out</a> about <a href="https://www.wsj.com/economy/the-u-s-can-afford-a-bigger-military-we-just-cant-build-it-7edd0e74">this problem</a> , because it puts the US in imminent danger of losing a major war to China.</p><p> But you know who can build ships? Japan and Korea. Together, our smallish Asian allies have shipbuilding industries whose combined size is <a href="https://www.thinkchina.sg/economy/us-expands-trade-dispute-chinas-shipbuilding-sector">almost as large as that of China</a> . And while Korea is bigger than Japan in terms of commercial shipbuilding, Japan can make complex high-tech naval vessels too, having just <a href="https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3258404/japan-gets-some-same-toys-big-boys-kaga-first-full-aircraft-carrier-wwii-enters-service">built its first true aircraft carrier</a> since WW2.</p><p>一个简单的解决方案展示了自己：为日本的美国海军建造船只。这将有助于在短期内解决美国的采购问题。通过增加对日本产品的需求，这也将有助于<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/is-japan-having-a-currency-crisis">加强日历</a>，从而防止货币市场中断，从而在关键时刻削弱美国关键的盟友。</p><p>这听起来像是一种太聪明且开箱即用的解决方案，无法伐木美国政府。但这不是！实际上，我们正在<a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/International-relations/Indo-Pacific/U.S.-seeks-to-integrate-Japan-into-defense-industrial-base">寻找现在做的方法</a>：</p><blockquote><p>美国总统乔·拜登（Joe Biden）和日本总理福米奥·基希田（Fumio Kishida）将同意探索各国国防行业之间的更紧密合作……该合作将不限于在日本私人造船厂维修美国海军船只，但也将设想共同开发和共同生产[美国政府]官员说……</p><p>日本国防工业基础的使用将从船舶维修开始……[C]资产的生产可能始于弹药。美国的弹药不足，必须将其提供给乌克兰和以色列。与日本国防工业共同制作的弹药将有助于回填印度太平洋的库存。</p></blockquote><p>我们需要急剧加速这一努力。美国海军舰船和潜艇，更不用说导弹盛行，需要尽快在日本造船厂滚开线路。韩国也应该参加这次谈话。</p><p>当然，这将是一个巨大的历史讽刺，因为美国通过大量超越日本赢得了第二次世界大战。但是时代和经济和联盟也会改变。日本的建筑船只与国防政策所获得的几乎不费吹灰之力。</p><h4> 5.右侧的契约</h4><p>如今，您经常听到科技人员抱怨进步人对新行业的热情，无论是莉娜·汗（Lina Khan）在FTC上反对大型技术的十字军东征，加里·加斯勒（Gary Gensler）在SEC上的关注对加密货币的关注，也是各种AI安全工作。但是，一些红色国家的州长提醒我们，保守主义可以像进步主义一样<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/dont-be-a-decel">减速</a>。佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯（Ron DeSantis）和阿拉巴马州州长凯·艾维（Kay Ivey）现已签署法律来<a href="https://www.vox.com/future-perfect/2024/5/8/24151435/john-fetterman-lab-grown-cultivated-meat-ron-desantis-florida-ban">禁止实验室成长的肉</a>：</p><blockquote><p>上周，佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯（Ron DeSantis）签署<a href="https://www.wired.com/story/lab-grown-fake-meat-ban-alabama-florida/">了</a>一项法案，以<a href="https://www.vox.com/future-perfect/2024/2/14/24069722/political-ban-cell-cultivated-lab-grown-meat-plant-based-labeling-laws">禁止</a>阳光州的细胞培养或“实验室成长”肉类。</p><p> DeSantis禁止该技术保护佛罗里达州的农民和牧场主免受未来的竞争。但这也是州长的文化战争，因为肉已经成为右翼负面政治的热门话题。 DeSantis签署了该法案的那一天，他在X上发布了一个<a href="https://twitter.com/GovRonDeSantis/status/1785684809467011431">奇怪的图像</a>，指责世界经济论坛的专制情节迫使人们吃细胞培养的肉。根据<a href="https://www.wired.com/story/lab-grown-fake-meat-ban-alabama-florida/">《连线》的</a>说法，一个称为阿拉巴马州健康自由的反疫苗组织提倡该州的细胞培养肉类禁令。</p></blockquote><p>奇怪的是，民主党参议员约翰·费特曼（John Fetterman）支持此举。</p><p>当然，实验室成长的肉是科技行业的一个很大的利基市场 - 它具有巨大的未来潜力，但它甚至还没有作为可行的商业市场而存在。但是电动汽车是一个巨大且快速增长的市场，也是科技行业的支柱。随着中国<a href="https://insideevs.com/features/719015/china-is-ahead-of-west/">为美国电动汽车行业的枪击</a>，美国车辆在全球范围内保持竞争力需要一定数量的反补贴。</p><p>输入<a href="https://fortune.com/2024/05/09/trump-electric-vehicles-oil-gas-climate-chevron-exxon/">唐纳德·J·特朗普</a>：</p><blockquote><p> <a href="https://fortune.com/2024/05/08/electric-vehicles-hybrids-internal-combustion-engines-sustainable-automotive-transport/">电动汽车</a>行业的命运可能取决于前总统唐纳德·特朗普的连任竞选。</p><p>根据<em><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2024/05/09/trump-oil-industry-campaign-money/">《华盛顿邮报》</a></em><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2024/05/09/trump-oil-industry-campaign-money/">的</a>一份报告， <a href="https://fortune.com/2024/05/06/hush-money-gag-order-catch-and-kill-dictionary-trump-new-york-criminal-trial/">特朗普</a>在佛罗里达州的一次会议上告诉一个充满石油高管的房间，换取他的连任竞选竞选活动10亿美元的竞选<a href="https://fortune.com/2024/03/20/epa-climate-rule-biden-emisions-curb-limit-electric-vehicles/">资金</a>。据报道，石油高管对特朗普评论的交易性质进行了抨击……</p><p>在未来的监管削减中包括一系列旨在鼓励汽车制造商投资和制造更多电动汽车的法规的承诺……如果特朗普的希望得以实现，他们可能会破坏一些精心制定的美国汽车制造商计划，这些计划是投资了投资的美国汽车制造商数十亿电动汽车。</p></blockquote><p>对电动汽车和实验室种植的肉的攻击应引起科技行业的明显提醒，即权利不是与<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/thoughts-on-techno-optimism">技术进步的事业</a>成为朋友的盟友。当所讨论的技术推动了正确的文化战争按钮时，共和党人将本能地响应欧洲耻辱的法规。</p><p>从我的角度来看，这很可悲。我们无法有两个自动对新发明持怀疑态度的政党。美国的工业未来以及其地缘政治安全 - 取决于全心全意地拥抱快速技术创新。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-a59?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-a59?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><h4></h4>; 
The macro arsonistsGovernments have borrowing constraints. Pretending otherwise is very dangerous. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-macro-arsonists https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-macro-arsonistsNoah Smith Wed, 08 May 2024 09:06:24 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg" width="712" height="455.21311475409834" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:663,&quot;width&quot;:1037,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:712,&quot;bytes&quot;:61561,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5688c0f0-bc3a-4c5b-a77b-2e8f85a17e59_1037x663.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://unsplash.com/@pawelj?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Pawel Janiak</a>摄于<a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/fire-burning-on-the-road-with-high-rise-buildings-during-daytime-photography-49LBMXrY5BE?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>近年来，被称为MMT的经济<a href="https://johnhcochrane.blogspot.com/2020/07/magical-monetary-theory-full-review.html">伪理论</a>在公众舆论中表现不佳。 MMT的基本戒律之一是，政府没有预算限制 - 阻止政府借贷和花费无限的钱的唯一一件事就是<em>通货膨胀</em>的风险。在2020年之前，当通货膨胀率上升和利率较低时，通货膨胀率低时，MMT人民能够在没有太多阻碍的情况下挥舞着这种危险。但是，自从通货膨胀于2021年爆炸回民族意识以来，财政赤字可以使一个国家无限制地生活的观念似乎是危险的，甚至是怪异的。</p><p> MMT人民通过做自己最擅长的事情来回应这种挫折 - 在批评者围绕他们的批评家中发起努力，并吸引了尚未通过苦涩的经验来避免他们的人。两年前，他们获得了《纽约时报》，给他们带来了<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-nyt-article-on-mmt-is-really">些许的hagiographic文章</a>。回击是如此凶猛，以至于报纸将标题更改为更中性的东西，但他们在《泰晤士报》上<a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=from%3Atalmonsmith%20mmt&amp;src=typed_query&amp;f=top">继续进行了一些侵害</a>。现在，他们制作了一部纪录片，<em>找到了钱</em>，倡导他们模糊的定义思想，并像往常一样呼唤 - 以获得更多的赤字支出。</p><p>在<em>找到这笔钱</em>时，MMT人民采访了拜登经济顾问委员会主席贾里德·伯恩斯坦（Jared Bernstein）。当他们问他为什么美国以我们印刷的货币借钱时，他偶然发现自己试图给出一个机智的答案。 MMT人们一直将其作为一个巨大的“陷阱”时刻。</p><p>进步主义者对MMT人民<a href="https://twitter.com/arindube/status/1786868675619786831">有理由生气</a>，但保守派却在发声。 Fox Business <a href="https://www.foxbusiness.com/politics/white-house-economic-adviser-struggles-with-question-on-monetary-policy">认为这是新闻价值的</a>，华盛顿自由信标甚至将剪辑放在其YouTube帐户上： </p><div id="youtube2-1Fj0zRmEWYc" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;1Fj0zRmEWYc&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/1Fj0zRmEWYc?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><p>这表明，如果进步主义者不愿倾听，MMT愿意将他们的无缺陷信息低语到保守派的耳朵中。这肯定符合他们的历史 - 该运动的现任面孔斯蒂芬妮·凯尔顿（Stephanie Kelton） <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/view/articles/2019-02-01/rich-must-embrace-deficits-to-escape-taxes">写道</a>，财政赤字是富人缴纳较低税款的一种方式，MMT的创始人对冲基金经理沃伦·莫斯勒（Warren Mosler），MMT的创始人， <a href="https://clintballinger.com/2021/01/11/a-very-oblique-history-of-mmt-part-ii-co-authors-mosler-etc/">从艺术拉弗</a>。</p><p>最终，MMT作为一项运动并不重要 - 经济新闻界最终将避开它们，就像伯尼·桑德斯（Bernie Sanders）和AOC在初次调情之后都一样。但是，他们颁布和代表的想法 - 赤字支出并没有真正损失纳税人的任何事情 - 夺走了自己的生活。我看到这个想法曾经证明诸如取消学生贷款之类的事情是合理的，理由是没有人真正付出法案： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg" width="928" height="247" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bd9c4eba-1d5a-41e0-a0b5-9ab05127094d_928x247.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:247,&quot;width&quot;:928,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:67870,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;t